Key Match Events: Mohamed Bayo scored the winning goal in the 8th minute of stoppage time
Equatorial Guinea were down to 10 men from the 55th minute onwards
Emilio Nsue missed a penalty for Equatorial Guinea
Post-Match Reflections: Guinea ended a long sequence of losing in the AFCON knockout stages
Guinea had the best chance of the first half but Aguibou Camara hesitated
Equatorial Guinea's Federico Bikoro was sent off for a high-foot tackle on Bayo
Miscellaneous Highlights: Mohamed Bayo plays for Le Havre in France's Ligue 1
Guinea had a 4-0 win against the Ivorians in the group stage
Guinea will face the winner of the Democratic Republic of Congo and Egypt match in the next round
